+    <div class="case-tag">Case Study · Local Payment On-Ramp</div>
+    <h1>A local payment on-ramp for <em>LatAm.</em></h1>
+    <p class="case-summary">
+      New users in Mexico, Argentina, and Colombia had one way to fund their first
+      account: a manual, peer-to-peer process that most never finished. I diagnosed
+      where the funnel was leaking, partnered with a payments provider, and shipped
+      a native bank-transfer flow. <strong>Spoiler alert: the impact is real.</strong>
+    </p>
+
+    <div class="case-meta" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr); gap: 20px;">
+      <div><div class="label">Role</div><div class="val">Product Manager (Lead)</div></div>
+      <div><div class="label">Markets</div><div class="val">MX · CO · AR</div></div>
+      <div><div class="label">Team</div><div class="val">16 — Partnerships, Legal, Compliance, Engineering, Regional Biz, Design</div></div>
+      <div><div class="label">Duration</div><div class="val">2–3 months</div></div>
+      <div><div class="label">Period</div><div class="val">2026</div></div>
+    </div>
+
+    <div class="case-hero-img" style="background:#0c0c0c; aspect-ratio: auto; display:block; padding:0; overflow:hidden;">
+      <img src="assets/latam_case_study_main.png" alt="Local payment on-ramp campaign"
+           style="width:100%;height:auto;display:block;border-radius:inherit;">
+    </div>
+
