+        <!-- i. POSITION IS EVERYTHING -->
+        <div class="case-section" id="ads-context">
+          <div class="num">i.</div>
+          <h2>Background</h2>
+
+          <div class="cs-disclaimer">Some business figures have been omitted / cannot be shared in actuality per confidentiality obligations.</div>
+
+          <p class="cs-lede">Paid placement is one of the oldest mechanics in digital commerce. We were sitting on it and not charging for it.</p>
+
+          <p>
+            Google built a $200B+ business on a simple insight: the top of a search results page is
+            the most valuable real estate on the internet. Businesses pay to appear there because
+            that's where the clicks go. Amazon runs the same playbook in product discovery —
+            sponsored listings at the top, organic results below. The model is universal: in any
+            ranked list, attention concentrates at the top, and concentrated attention can be
+            monetised.
+          </p>
+
+          <p>
+            Our P2P marketplace works the same way. Takers open the app, see a list of merchants
+            offering to buy or sell crypto, and pick from near the top. There's no algorithm
+            surfacing a "best match" — just a ranked list, and rank determines volume. A merchant
+            at position 1 sees far more trades than one at position 5. That's the same structural
+            dynamic as Google Search and Amazon — just applied to a crypto exchange.
+          </p>
+
+          <p>
+            Our merchants already understood this intuitively. They were fighting for the top
+            position constantly — refreshing rates, monitoring their rank, pulling listings when
+            pushed down. The demand for paid visibility was real and measurable.
+            <strong>We just weren't charging for it.</strong>
+          </p>
+        </div>
+
