+
+          <div class="cs-disclaimer">Some business figures have been omitted / cannot be shared in actuality per confidentiality obligations.</div>
+
+          <p class="cs-lede">We flew to Vietnam to meet our merchants. What we found changed how we thought about the entire product.</p>
+
+          <p>
+            P2P trading on crypto exchanges isn't just used by individuals moving small amounts.
+            In Vietnam — one of our fastest growing regions — a class of professional merchants
+            had emerged: operators running P2P as a core business. They held large crypto
+            inventories, managed multiple bank accounts, processed dozens of orders a day,
+            and had built internal systems to keep up with the volume.
+          </p>
+
+          <p>
+            The biggest ones were processing up to <strong>$1M USDT per day</strong> on our platform alone —
+            and many were simultaneously active on multiple exchanges.
+            They weren't casual traders. They were running operations.
+          </p>
+
+          <p>
+            Collectively, this group of top-tier merchants accounted for roughly
+            <strong>~70% of total P2P trading volume in Vietnam</strong>.
+            That made them the single biggest lever for regional liquidity. Our north star
+            was straightforward: increase their trading volume. If we could remove the
+            operational friction holding them back, regional volume would follow.
+          </p>
+        </div>
